<h1>About Psychology</h1>
<font face="monospace" size="4"><p>The science of psychology is the study of how the brain, environment, and behavior relate to each other. Psychologists use the scientific method to collect and analyze data to improve lives and solve problems. Psychology is the scientific study of the mind and behavior. It delves into various facets of human thought processes, emotions, motivations, and actions. By understanding psychology, we gain valuable insights into why individuals behave the way they do and how they interact with others.<br><br>

<b>Subfields of Psychology</b>
<b>Cognitive psychology</b><br>
Studies mental processes like memory, thinking, and learning<br> <br>

<b>Abnormal psychology</b><br>
Studies abnormal behavior and mental disorders<br><br> 

<b>Biological psychology</b><br>
Studies how biological processes affect the mind <br><br>

<b>Health psychology</b><br>
Uses psychology to promote health, prevent illness, and improve health care <br><br>

<b>Personality psychology</b><br>
Studies the nature, development, and structure of personality 
<br><br>
<b>Behavioral psychology</b><br>
Studies how to change human behavior through analysis and therapyÂ <br><br>
 

